clinical_study.brief_title: Study Comparing 13-valent Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine With 7-valent Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine
clinical_study.official_title: A Phase 3, Randomized, Active-Controlled, Double-blind Trial Evaluating the Safety, Tolerability and Immunologic Noninferiority of a 13-valent Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine Compared to a 7-valent Pneumococcal Conjugate Vaccine in Healthy Infants Given With Routine Pediatric Vaccinations in the United States

brief_summary.textblock: The purpose of this study is to evaluate the safety, tolerability, and immunogenicity of the 13-valent pneumococcal vaccine (13vPnC) compare to the 7-valent pneumococcal vaccine (7vPnC) and to compare the immune response to concomitant vaccines administered with 13vPnC and 7vPnC.

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Achieving Antibody Level ≥0.35 μg/mL in 13vPnC Group Relative to 7vPnC Group After the 3-Dose Infant Series
primary_outcome.time_frame: One month after the 3-dose infant series (7 months of age)
primary_outcome.description: Percentages of Participants achieving World Health Organization (WHO) predefined antibody threshold ≥0.35 μg/mL along with the corresponding 95% CI for the 7 common pneumococcal serotypes (serotypes 4, 6B, 9V, 14, 18C, 19F, and 23F) and 6 additional pneumococcal serotypes specific to 13vPnC (serotypes 1, 3, 5, 6A, 7F, and 19A) are presented.

primary_outcome.measure: Geometric Mean Antibody Concentration in 13vPnC Group Relative to 7vPnC Group 1 Month After the Toddler Dose
primary_outcome.description: Antibody concentration/geometric mean concentration as measured by enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) for 7 common pneumococcal serotypes (serotypes 4, 6B, 9V, 14, 18C, 19F, and 23F) and 6 additional pneumococcal serotypes specific to 13vPnC (Serotypes 1, 3, 5, 6A, 7F, and 19A) are presented.

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Achieving Predefined Antibody Levels for Haemophilus Influenzae Type b, Diphtheria Toxoid, and Pertussis Antigens in 13vPnC Group Relative to 7vPnC Group After the Infant Series
primary_outcome.time_frame: One Month After the Infant Series (7 months of age)
primary_outcome.description: Predefined Antibody Levels for Haemophilus Influenzae Type b ([Hib] 0.15 µg/mL or 1.0 µg/mL), Diphtheria Toxoid (0.1 International Units [IU]/mL), and Pertussis antigens (Pertussis filamentous hemagglutinin [FHA] 40.5 Elisa Units [EU]/mL, Pertussis toxoid [PT] 16.5 EU/mL, Pertussis pertactin [PRN] 26 EU/mL).

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Reporting Pre-specified Systemic Events
primary_outcome.description: Systemic events (any fever [Fv] ≥ 38 degrees Celsius [C], decreased (decr.) appetite, irritability, increased (incr.) sleep, decreased sleep, and hives [urticaria], use of antipyretic medication [med] to treat or prevent symptoms [sx]) were reported using an electronic diary. Participants may be represented in more than 1 category.

primary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Reporting Pre-specified Local Reactions
primary_outcome.description: Local reactions were reported using an electronic diary. Tenderness was scaled as Any (tenderness present); Significant ([Sig.], present and interfered with limb movement). Redness and swelling were scaled as Any (redness or swelling present); Mild (0.5 centimeters [cm] to 2.0 cm); Moderate ([Mod.], 2.5 to 7.0 cm); Severe ([Sev.], > 7.0 cm). Participants may have been represented in more than 1 category.

secondary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Achieving Predefined Antibody Levels for Concomitant Vaccine Antigens Induced by Measles, Mumps, Rubella, Varicella (MMR-V) and Haemophilus Influenzae Type b (Hib)
secondary_outcome.time_frame: One month after toddler dose (13 to 16 months of age)

secondary_outcome.measure: Geometric Mean Antibody Concentration of Hib PRP in 13vPnC Group Relative to 7vPnC Group After the Toddler Dose
secondary_outcome.time_frame: one month after the toddler dose

secondary_outcome.measure: Geometric Mean Antibody Concentration of Measles, Mumps, and Varicella ELISA in 13vPnC Group Relative to 7vPnC Group After the Toddler Dose
secondary_outcome.time_frame: one month after the toddler dose
secondary_outcome.description: Normalization was performed for unit of measure "index value" as Index Value of 1.00 = 10 mIU/mL.

secondary_outcome.measure: Geometric Mean Antibody Concentration of Rubella in 13vPnC Group Relative to 7vPnC Group After the Toddler Dose
secondary_outcome.time_frame: one month after the toddler dose

secondary_outcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Achieving Functional Antibody Titer ≥1:8 as Measured by Opsonophagocytic Activity Assay (OPA) in 13vPnC Group Relative to 7vPnC Group the 3-Dose Infant Series and the Toddler Dose
secondary_outcome.time_frame: One month after infant series and one month after toddler dose
secondary_outcome.description: Percentage of participants achieving functional antibody titer ≥1:8 as measured by opsonophagocytic activity assay (OPA) along with the corresponding 95% CI for the 7 common pneumococcal serotypes (serotypes 4, 6B, 9V, 14, 18C, 19F, and 23F) and 6 additional pneumococcal serotypes specific to 13vPnC (serotypes 1, 3, 5, 6A, 7F, and 19A) are presented.

secondary_outcome.measure: Geometric Mean Titer (GMT) as Measured by Opsonophagocytic Activity Assay (OPA) in 13vPnC Group Relative to 7vPnC Group After the 3-Dose Infant Series and the Toddler Dose
secondary_outcome.time_frame: one month after the infant series and the toddler dose
secondary_outcome.description: Geometric mean titer (GMT) as measured by opsonophagocytic activity assay (OPA) for 7 common pneumococcal serotypes (serotypes 4, 6B, 9V, 14, 18C, 19F, and 23F) and 6 additional pneumococcal serotypes specific to 13vPnC (Serotypes 1, 3, 5, 6A, 7F, and 19A) are presented.

intervention.description: 1 single 0.5 mL dose together with a concomitant dose of Pediarix and ActHIB at the 2-, 4-, and 6-month visits and ProQuad, PedvaxHIB, and VAQTA at the 12-15 month visit.
1 single 0.5 mL dose together with a concomitant dose of Pediarix and ActHIB at the 2-, 4-, and 6-month visits and ProQuad, PedvaxHIB, and VAQTA at the 12-15 month visit.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Healthy 2-month-old infants.
- Available for the entire study period.
Exclusion criteria:
- Previous vaccination with any vaccine before the start of the study.
- Known contraindication to vaccination.

overall_official.affiliation: Wyeth is now a wholly owned subsidiary of Pfizer

participant_flow.recruitment_details: Participants were recruited in the United States from September 2006 to January 2008.
participant_flow.pre_assignment_details: Participants were enrolled into the study according to inclusion/exclusion criteria without a screening period.

group.title: 13vPnC
group.description: Participants received one single 0.5 mL dose of 13-valent pneumococcal conjugate vaccine (13vPnC) coadministered with Haemophilus b Conjugate Vaccine (ActHIB) and Diphtheria and Tetanus Toxoids and Acellular Pertussis Adsorbed, Hepatitis B (Recombinant) and Inactivated Poliovirus Vaccine Combined (Pediarix) at 2, 4, 6 months (infant series). Participants received one single 0.5 mL dose of 13vPnC coadministered with measles, mumps, rubella varicella vaccine live (ProQuad), Haemophilus b Conjugate Vaccine (Meningococcal Protein Conjugate) (PedvaxHIB), and Hepatitis A Vaccine, Inactivated (VAQTA) at 12-15 months of age (toddler dose).
